name: Helsingør Bibliotek/Kulturværftet
directions: All gender neutral bathrooms are in the library itself. The library is in three floor, first floor - children's section - and a gender neutral kids bathroom with changing table, second and third have three gender neutral bathrooms each, one of them for disabled users. All floors are accessible by elevator for people who can't manage stairs,
comment: Everyone can in the library's open hours go up into the library itself and use the bathrooms, not permit or anything needed.

name: Cataroqui Town Center

On the upper level, there is a large, accessible single-occupancy gender-neutral washroom inside Marshall's; it's usually empty.
Also, in the food court on the lower level, there are male and female washrooms, then a family one that anyone can use.

name: Tate Hall
directions:
From East entrance: go down left staircase, walk down the corridor and turn left. The bathroom is immediately to the left. Door marked B00-20, has handicap access button and an occupied/vacant marker on the door.

There is a second gender neutral restroom on the 3rd floor. This can be reached by ascending the staircase in the south-west corner of the building to the 3rd floor and the bathroom will be immediately in front of you. Alternatively, take the elevator to the 3rd floor, exit and turn left. Make your first right and you will pass the men's room on your left. Behind the men's room on your left you will find the bathroom. This room is accessible and not too frequently occupied.
comment: Primarily students in the area, but the building is publicly accessable.
